Hello,

I have created a php script which runs in an endless loop:

while(true){
  Connect()
  LoginWithPassword()
  //send and receive messages for sometime
  Disconnect()
  //wait some time
}

Everything works fine, but wenn the loop starts for the second time, connect and login SEEM to be successful, but actually the account is still OFFLINE.

As far as I understand, Disconnect() closes the socket and Connect() opens a socket. But there ist no "logout" function...

Can anyone explain, why this isn't working and how to fix it?

Thanks in advance!

comment_data.body:
Should have been fixed according to https://github.com/venomous0x/WhatsAPI/issues/321

Can you post the XML output you get after reconnect?
```php
echo "<textarea>";
$w = new WhatsProt($username, $identity, $nickname, true);
$w->connect();
$w->loginWithPassword($password);
$w->pollMessages();
$w->disconnect();
$w->connect();
$w->loginWithPassword($password);
$w->pollMessages();
```

Is there a particular reason why you would reconnect every time rather than keeping the same connection open and using a loop which calls pollMessages()?
```php
while(true)
{
    $w->pollMessages();
    sleep(1);
}
```

EDIT
Just tested it on my end, getting the proper response after reconnect:
```php
$w->connect();
$w->loginWithPassword($password);
$w->pollMessages();
$w->disconnect();
$w->connect();
$w->loginWithPassword($password);
$w->pollMessages();
```

The idea was to make the whatsapp server think I was a "real" smartphone which is switched off for a short time every two or three days - to avoid being blocked one day...

@shirioko I also get a proper response after reconnect - but actually I am offline and can't send or receive messages

@assegaf So, how do I send an unvailable status?

@antonella18 yes, because you're constantly sending messages to the servers.

the server stops replying to you after 5 minutes of receiving inactivity. So, if you send an inactive presence, after 5 minutes of not receiving anything, the server will stop caring about your messages being sent and you will receive absolutely nothing in return (the server won't immediately disconnect you though), and you'll be forced to reauth.

also, please consider not using this if it's a spam script. =) Honestly.
